    "notes": [
      {
        "category": "summary",
        "text": "An update is available for device-mapper-multipath.\nThis update affects Rocky Linux 9.\nA Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE list",
        "title": "Topic"
      },
      {
        "category": "description",
        "text": "The device-mapper-multipath packages provide tools that use the device-mapper multipath kernel module to manage multipath devices.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* device-mapper-multipath: Regression of CVE-2022-41974 fix in Rocky Linux (CVE-2022-3787)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n\nThis advisory is provided by Ctrl IQ, Inc for Rocky Linux systems. For more information about CIQ security practices, visit https://ciq.com/security.",
        "title": "Description"
      }
    ],
